# Axodus Portfolio Sprint 01 Allocation

Last updated: 2026-06-04

Baseline: RECAST 01 - Nucleus Maturity Audit & Baseline Register.

Sprint objective: convert the RECAST 01 maturity baseline into a balanced next-request allocation without allowing over-advancement of mature or execution-sensitive nuclei.

## Allocation Policy

- Recovery work receives first priority.
- L3/L4 advancement is allowed only through documentation, contracts, read models, validation plans, and mock/read-only boundaries.
- L5 nuclei are not accelerated unless the work is backlog control, gap analysis, or non-executing documentation.
- HOLD nuclei do not advance implementation in this sprint.
- No production execution, trading, swaps, settlement, treasury, payouts, wallet signing, credentials, or on-chain writes are approved.

