## Allocation Bias

| Category | Target Bias | Assigned Priority Range |
|---|---:|---|
| Recovery work | 40% | Priorities 1-4 |
| L3/L4 controlled advancement | 35% | Priorities 5-11 |
| HOLD/backlog control | 15% | Priorities 12-15 |
| Portfolio governance/documentation | 10% | Global docs, report, queue, roadmap/status/blockers |

## Dependencies

- REQ-01 should precede broad root/global docs changes because `/opt/Axodus` is not a Git repository.
- REQ-02 should precede production-facing Documentation claims.
- REQ-03 and REQ-04 should precede any BBA/Lottery production-like route or claim expansion.
- REQ-05 must precede DEX UI visibility implementation and must keep swaps/settlement disabled.
- REQ-06 should precede Mining payout/provider integration work.
- REQ-07 through REQ-11 are contract/readiness planning only and must not enable real execution.
- REQ-12 through REQ-15 are backlog-control requests and should not compete for implementation priority while recovery work is open.

## Final Boundary

This allocation does not approve runtime features, production configs, credentials, installs, builds, services, live trading, swaps, settlement, treasury movement, payouts, wallet signing, on-chain writes, vendor mutation, or token-list changes.
